abstract: He was convinced that human beings would eventually connect with extraterrestrials, and he inspired others to share that belief.
snippet: He was convinced that human beings would eventually connect with extraterrestrials, and he inspired others to share that belief.
lead_paragraph: Frank Drake, who pointed a radio telescope at a pair of stars in 1960 hoping to find alien civilizations and thus kindled a continuing endeavor called the Search for Extraterrestrial Intelligence, or SETI, died on Friday at his home in Aptos, Calif. He was 92.

main: Frank Drake, Who Led Search for Life on Other Planets, Dies at 92
print_headline: Frank Drake, 92, Hopeful Earthling Who Reached Out to the Stars, Dies

abstract: Efforts to help Ukraine shield its cities may depend on the scarcity of both Russian missiles and Western air defense systems.
snippet: Efforts to help Ukraine shield its cities may depend on the scarcity of both Russian missiles and Western air defense systems.
lead_paragraph: With a new wave of Russian airstrikes this week that slammed into the capital and more than a dozen other cities, Western officials are under increasing pressure to speed the delivery of missiles, launchers and other sophisticated air defense systems to help protect Ukraine.

main: Can Russia Keep Firing Missiles at Cities? And What Defenses Does Ukraine Need?
print_headline: How Long Can Russia Keep Firing Missiles?

abstract: The internet giant said it would begin testing its new chatbot, Bard, with a small, private group before releasing it to the public in the coming weeks.
snippet: The internet giant said it would begin testing its new chatbot, Bard, with a small, private group before releasing it to the public in the coming weeks.
lead_paragraph: Google said on Monday that it would soon release an experimental chatbot called Bard as it races to respond to ChatGPT, which has wowed millions of people since it was unveiled at the end of November.

main: Racing to Catch Up With ChatGPT, Google Plans Release of Its Own Chatbot
print_headline: Google Plans Its Chatbot  In Response To ChatGPT

original: By Cade Metz and Nico Grant

abstract: An F.B.I. raid on the home of Donald Trump.
snippet: An F.B.I. raid on the home of Donald Trump.
lead_paragraph: The F.B.I. searched Donald Trump’s Palm Beach, Fla., home, including a safe that agents broke open, the former U.S. president said yesterday — an account signaling a dramatic escalation in the various investigations into the final stages of his presidency. The search appeared to be focused on files that Trump had brought to Florida when he left the White House.

abstract: A popular show on Netflix is about the glamorous job of a U.S. ambassador. But is it realistic?
snippet: A popular show on Netflix is about the glamorous job of a U.S. ambassador. But is it realistic?
lead_paragraph: The allure of an ambassador’s life is obvious: wielding government power and throwing parties for influential people in a far-flung location. “The Diplomat,” which premiered last month on Netflix, highlights the glamour while omitting the drudgery of the job — the memos, press engagements and red tape.

lead_paragraph: Every Tuesday and Friday, Ezra Klein invites you into a conversation about something that matters, like today’s episode with Michelle Goldberg. Listen wherever you get your podcasts.

main: Transcript: Ezra Klein Interviews Michelle Goldberg

abstract: The implosion of Three Arrows Capital, a cryptocurrency hedge fund, devastated the industry. Its two founders spent the next year surfing, meditating and traveling the world.
snippet: The implosion of Three Arrows Capital, a cryptocurrency hedge fund, devastated the industry. Its two founders spent the next year surfing, meditating and traveling the world.
lead_paragraph: Not long after his cryptocurrency hedge fund collapsed last year, spawning a market meltdown that devastated the industry, Kyle Davies got on a plane and left his troubles behind.

main: Their Crypto Company Collapsed. They Went to Bali.
print_headline: Their Crypto Fund Collapsed Overnight. They Went to Bali.

abstract: Countries across the continent saw the warmest start to the year ever measured. The weather has forced ski resorts to close trails, with sparser than usual snow cover.
snippet: Countries across the continent saw the warmest start to the year ever measured. The weather has forced ski resorts to close trails, with sparser than usual snow cover.
lead_paragraph: In the coastal Spanish town of San Sebastián, residents swapped coats for T-shirts and headed to the beach for a swim. In Rome, tourists and locals strolled in the sunshine in light sweaters. And in low-lying areas of the Pyrenees, a lack of snowfall forced some French ski resorts to close trails.

main: Some in Europe Toasted the New Year in T-Shirts
print_headline: Welcoming the New Year In T-Shirts Across Europe

abstract: The Florida governor’s plan to announce his presidential campaign on the social network is the latest sign of the company’s efforts to court conservatives.
snippet: The Florida governor’s plan to announce his presidential campaign on the social network is the latest sign of the company’s efforts to court conservatives.
lead_paragraph: Gov. Ron DeSantis of Florida is expected to finally announce his presidential campaign on Wednesday night — but not on a stalwart of conservative media, like Fox News. Instead, the Republican star will do so live on Twitter, in a conversation with Elon Musk. (Fox News will get the first television interview with Mr. DeSantis afterward.)

main: DeSantis’s Big Event Underscores a Rightward Move for Twitter
